      <title>Roots of polynomial</title>
      <link href="/2020/06/24/Roots-of-polynomial/"/>
      <url>/2020/06/24/Roots-of-polynomial/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Relations-of-the-roots-in-polynomial-equations"><a href="#Relations-of-the-roots-in-polynomial-equations" class="headerlink" title="Relations of the roots in polynomial equations"></a>Relations of the roots in polynomial equations</h1><p> i. Quadratics $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$, with roots $\alpha, \beta$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sum \alpha = - \frac{b}{a}, \qquad \sum \alpha \beta = \frac{c}{a}.</script><p> ii. Cubics $ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d = 0$, with roots $\alpha, \beta, \gamma$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sum \alpha = - \frac{b}{a}, \qquad \sum \alpha \beta = \frac{c}{a}, \qquad  \sum \alpha \beta \gamma = -\frac{d}{a}.</script><p> iii. Quartics  $ax^4 + bx^3 + cx^2 + dx + e = 0$, with roots $\alpha, \beta, \gamma, \delta$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sum \alpha = - \frac{b}{a}, \qquad \sum \alpha \beta = \frac{c}{a}, \qquad  \sum \alpha \beta \gamma = -\frac{d}{a}, \qquad \sum \alpha \beta \gamma \delta= \frac{e}{a}.</script><a id="more"></a><p> iv. Quantic with higher order $ax^n + bx^{n-1} + \cdots + k = 0$, </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sum \alpha = - \frac{b}{a}, \qquad \sum \alpha \beta \gamma \cdots= (-1)^n \frac{last term}{first term} = (-1)^n\frac{k}{a}.</script><hr><hr><h1 id="Special-cases-for-cubic-equation-with-roots-alpha-beta-gamma"><a href="#Special-cases-for-cubic-equation-with-roots-alpha-beta-gamma" class="headerlink" title="Special cases for cubic equation with roots  $\alpha, \beta, \gamma$."></a>Special cases for cubic equation with roots  $\alpha, \beta, \gamma$.</h1><p>i. $S_2$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned}\sum \alpha^2 = \alpha^2 + \beta^2 + \gamma^2 & = (\alpha + \beta + \gamma )^2 - 2(\alpha\beta + \beta \gamma + \alpha \gamma) \\& = (\sum \alpha)^2 - 2 \sum \alpha \beta \end{aligned}</script><p>ii. </p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned} \sum \alpha^2 \beta ^2 = \alpha^2 \beta ^2 +  \beta ^2 \gamma^2 + \alpha^2 \gamma ^2 &= (\alpha\beta + \beta\gamma + \alpha\gamma)^2 -  2\alpha\beta\gamma(\alpha + \beta + \gamma) \\&= \big(\sum \alpha\beta \big)^2 - 2\sum \alpha \sum \alpha\beta\gamma. \end{aligned}</script><p>iii.  $S_{-1}$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\sum \frac{1}{\alpha} = \frac{1}{\alpha} + \frac{1}{\beta} + \frac{1}{\gamma} = \frac{\alpha\beta + \beta\gamma + \alpha\gamma}{\alpha\beta\gamma}= \frac{\sum \alpha\beta}{\sum \alpha\beta\gamma}.</script><p>iv. $S_3$</p><script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned}\sum \alpha^3 = \alpha^3 + \beta^3 + \gamma^3 &= (\alpha + \beta + \gamma) \big((\alpha + \beta + \gamma)^2 - 3(\alpha\beta + \beta\gamma + \alpha\gamma)\big) + 3 \alpha\beta\gamma \\&= \sum \alpha \big((\sum \alpha)^2 - 3 \sum \alpha\beta \big) + 3 \sum \alpha\beta\gamma. \end{aligned}</script>]]></content>
      
      
