        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Installment"><a href="#Installment" class="headerlink" title="Installment"></a>Installment</h1><ul><li>python  need to download some code, <em>copy and paste to form get_pip.py</em></li><li>MiKTex </li><li>SOX</li><li>ffmpeg</li><li>pycairo <em>notice: the version should be the same with python</em></li></ul><a id="more"></a><p>When all finished, run </p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="comment">#!/usr/bin/env python3</span></span><br><span class="line">python -m install -r requirement.txt</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><strong>Test</strong>:<br>To test whether everything is ok, just type</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"> <span class="comment"># This is an animation made to show the process</span></span><br><span class="line">python -m manim example_scenes.py SquareTocircle -pl</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h1 id="FAQ"><a href="#FAQ" class="headerlink" title="FAQ"></a>FAQ</h1><ul><li>What is config.</li><li>Change background color</li><li>Remove background stroke with width of texts </li></ul><hr><h1 id="TEXT-FORMAT"><a href="#TEXT-FORMAT" class="headerlink" title="TEXT FORMAT"></a>TEXT FORMAT</h1><p>Turtorial material, notice </p><h2 id="text"><a href="#text" class="headerlink" title="text"></a>text</h2><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">python manim.py tutorial\<span class="number">1</span>_text_format.py -pl</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Remark: it is also ok to run in VISUAL studio code</p><h2 id="Position"><a href="#Position" class="headerlink" title="Position"></a>Position</h2><ul><li>absolute position</li><li>relative position  <ul><li>notice: the difference with “move to”  and “next to”</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="Grid"><a href="#Grid" class="headerlink" title="Grid"></a>Grid</h2><h2 id="line-4-92-copy-paste"><a href="#line-4-92-copy-paste" class="headerlink" title="- line 4-92 copy + paste"></a>- line 4-92 copy + paste</h2><p>When everything is finished, you can try “text_format.py” to see all kinds of settings.</p><h1 id="TEX-Formula"><a href="#TEX-Formula" class="headerlink" title="TEX Formula"></a>TEX Formula</h1><ul><li>Notice the difference with “TextMobject()” and “TexMoject”</li><li>For pure tex. just add TexMobject(r”\int_S (g+k)dm “)</li><li>for pure text, just add TextMobject(“contents”)</li><li>for mixed, just add TextMobject( “Suppose $ \\int_S (f+g)dm $”)</li><li>for mixed, if nicer, add TextMobject( “Suppose $ \\displaystyle\\int_S (f+g)dm  $”)</li></ul><hr><h1 id="Arrays"><a href="#Arrays" class="headerlink" title="Arrays"></a>Arrays</h1><ul><li>Notice the differnece with “norm_text” and “array_text”: assignment value in one block or differents blocks.<br>for array_text, one can assign value in array_text[0], array_text[1], …</li><li><p>Set color: text[0].set_color(RED)</p></li><li><p>**Problem: How to type chinese”</p></li><li><p>sqaure use two blocks to represent colors</p></li><li><p>End a formula, add . at the end.</p></li><li><p>notice the difference between {a”,”\\over”,”b} and \\frac{a}{b}</p></li><li><p>notice {} to be added if you want to consider them as a whole.</p></li><li><p><a href="https://github.com/Elteoremadebeethoven/MyAnimations/blob/master/check_formula_by_txt/Manual_CheckFormulaByTXT.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="order">Check formula</a> </p></li><li><p>use for to loop, sometimes it is convenient.</p><p>you can even try:</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">  <span class="comment"># !text color</span></span><br><span class="line">  <span class="keyword">for</span> i,color <span class="keyword">in</span> [(<span class="number">2</span>,RED),(<span class="number">4</span>,PINK)]: <span class="comment"># sometimes you can try zip</span></span><br><span class="line">      text[i].set_color(color)</span><br><span class="line">   ``` </span><br><span class="line">- [x] *args <span class="keyword">and</span> **kwargs <span class="keyword">in</span> Function Calls. </span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">  [*args](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-args-<span class="keyword">and</span>-kwargs-<span class="keyword">in</span>-python<span class="number">-3</span> <span class="string">"order"</span>)</span><br><span class="line">  </span><br><span class="line">- check box still next work properly.</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">---</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Transformation</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">-  Transform `self.play(Transform(texto1,texto2))`  </span><br><span class="line">-  Replacement `self.play(ReplacementTransform(text1,text2))`</span><br><span class="line">-  notice the difference between transform <span class="keyword">and</span> replacementtransform</span><br><span class="line">-  Copy Content `ReplacementTransform(formula[<span class="number">2</span>].copy(),formula[<span class="number">8</span>]),`  .copy needed!</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">-  Change color <span class="keyword">and</span> size: more useful to use</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">   ```python</span><br><span class="line">   text_generate_target()</span><br><span class="line">   text.target.shift(RIGHT*<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">   text.target.scale(<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">   text.target.set_color(RED)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">   self.play(</span><br><span class="line">     MoveToTarget(text)</span><br><span class="line">     run_time=<span class="number">2</span></span><br><span class="line">   )</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul><h1 id="Visual-Tools"><a href="#Visual-Tools" class="headerlink" title="Visual Tools"></a>Visual Tools</h1><h1 id="Introduction-to-2-D-graphs"><a href="#Introduction-to-2-D-graphs" class="headerlink" title="Introduction to 2-D graphs"></a>Introduction to 2-D graphs</h1><h1 id="Introduction-to-3-D-graphs"><a href="#Introduction-to-3-D-graphs" class="headerlink" title="Introduction to 3-D graphs"></a>Introduction to 3-D graphs</h1><h1 id="Add-audio"><a href="#Add-audio" class="headerlink" title="Add audio"></a>Add audio</h1><h1 id="Insert-pictures-and-SVGs"><a href="#Insert-pictures-and-SVGs" class="headerlink" title="Insert pictures and SVGs"></a>Insert pictures and SVGs</h1><h1 id="First-Project"><a href="#First-Project" class="headerlink" title="First Project"></a>First Project</h1>]]></content>
      
      
